Parking and Transportation Services






















												Visitors
					
Daily permits can be purchased at any parking dispensers located on campus. Enjoy your visit!
















												Purchase a Permit
					
Buy your Semester, Academic Year- General/Commuter and Resident Student permit here! 
















												Pay Citation
					
The easiest way is to pay online! Payments can also be made by mail.
















												Appeal Citation
					
Appeals must be submitted within 21 days from issuance of the citation or 14 days from mailing of the reminder notice. The appeal process is conducted pursuant to California Vehicle Code.
















												Free Bus Transit Options
					
Looking for a better way to get to campus? You've come to the right place! When you share the ride everyone benefits; the environment, your car, and your wallet! 
















												10 Commuter Link
					
The 10 Commuter Link is a weekday (M-F) service assisting the CSUSB community traveling to and from the Coachella Valley for FREE! All you need is your Coyote OneCard.















 
Spring Semester and Student Annual Parking Permits Are Now Available
 
PURCHASE PARKING PERMIT
Our Vision
Our vision is to provide effective and efficient parking and transportation services that maximize value, meet our customer's expectations, and maintain sustainability. 
Our Mission Statement
The University Police Department strives to provide "Quality Service" by providing professional service with honor, integrity, and a commitment to excellence to the community. We perform our mission through diligent crime prevention, victim assistance and emergency response preparedness. We believe campus safety is a community effort and embrace a community partnership and problem-oriented policing philosophy. We strive daily to live by our department motto, "Campus Safety through Service."
 
General Parking Information 

Parking permits are required seven days a week.  Parking permits continue to be required for any vehicle parked on campus overnight. Parking enforcement will continue at all times for disabled parking, service vehicle/other specially marked spaces, and fire zones.
 A special permit/decal is required to park in carpool spaces and residential spaces. Carpool permits require registration with the Transportation Services Department. The Transportation Services Department can be reached at (909) 537-7433 or rideshare@csusb.edu. 
 
Questions:
University Hall Room 039
Telephone: (909) 537-5912
Email: parking@csusb.edu
